<br>
In other words, use the /assist playername with or without a macro.<br>
<br>
You will either:<br>
1)  Get the message &quot;I don't see anyone by that name around here&quot; - the puller is too far away, and the /assist didn't work.<br>
2)  Get the message &quot;You cannot see the target!&quot; - the puller is in range, but your view of the mob is obscured - it didn't work, try again.<br>
3) No message, but nothing appears in your target window - it worked!  When the target gets close, it will appear in your target window.  You will see its name above it highlighted yellow (meaning you have it selected) before it gets close enough to appear in your target window.<br>
<br>
And /agree Genshin, /stick is very useful, and kind of funny to watch.<br>
